Most modern versions understand this expression here as a straight reference to the household of Saul, what could have support in v.4.

The exact meaning of בַּיִת here is discussed | it depends much on which meaning is attributed to נְוַת, usually seen as referring to women. NIV "in the camps men..." | Dahood (Psalms II: 51-100) "the country's pasture land".

LEXSense.DefinitionShort: = construction surrounded by walls and covered with a roof; ◄ normally made of stones, wood, or clay; ► to be used as living quarters, for storage, as a prison, as a sanctuary, etc.; sometimes used to denote a smaller part of a large construction
literally: house (of an object); hence: = a place that is associated with a certain class people that live there, or objects that are found there
literally: house (of an object); hence: = an object that serves as a holder or container of another object, ◄ as if it were its house
literally: house; hence: = a group of people associated with a house, such as the family living there, or the descendants of the head of the household
= relation linking a proposition to a location: the part of an object that is visible from the perspective of someone located within that object
